{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QQ1979oKDvb4WE1yLtr4z2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me execute what's needed:\n\n1. Create `app-user` with `readWrite` on `appdb`\n2. Create `reportingRole` custom role on `appdb` that allows read access to `appdb.reports` (aggregate should succeed)\n3. Grant `readonly-user` the `reportingRole` in addition to their existing `read` on `appdb`\n\nFor the `reportingRole`, the task says \"aggregate should succeed\" so I need to include the `aggregate` action on `appdb.reports`. Also the task says \"read access to appdb.reports\" - I should include `find` and `aggregate` at minimum.\nNow I'll execute all the required operations in a single mongosh session using the primary node, creating the custom role with the appropriate privileges, setting up the app-user account, and updating readonly-user with the new role.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":201,"cache_read_input_tokens":36201,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":201},"output_tokens":19,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dad8c38-f7f9-4b29-a20f-bfe5c5522b33","uuid":"2fc297b0-2e26-4725-8cdc-cb60c896cb46","request_id":"req_011Ccf44uwDY2a965uLudBxa"}
