{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015cGWkcCnLJXd6FPpD9gSPK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"MongoDB 6.0 doesn't support `aggregate` as a separate privilege action in this way. The `aggregate` privilege in MongoDB is part of the `find` action on a collection - if a user can `find`, they can also `aggregate`. Actually, wait - let me check what actions are valid for collection-level privileges in MongoDB 6.\n\nIn MongoDB, the valid actions for collection-level privileges include:\n- find\n- insert\n- update\n- remove\n- createIndex\n- dropIndex\n- createCollection\n- dropCollection\n- renameCollectionSameDB\n- etc.\n\nActually, `aggregate` is a valid action in newer MongoDB versions. \n\nThe error message \"Unrecognized action: aggregate\" suggests that either the MongoDB version doesn't support it as a standalone action, or the syntax is wrong. In MongoDB 6.0, the `aggregate` command is typically controlled through the `find` privilege on the collections being accessed, though newer versions do support `aggregate` as its own action. Let me verify what's actually available in version 6.0 specifically. I think the real issue is that `find` is the privilege I actually need here, not `aggregate`. The `aggregate` action might be for something else entirely, or it's not available in this MongoDB version. Let me simplify and just use `find` for the reporting role since that's what actually grants permission to run aggregation pipelines on collections.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1019,"cache_read_input_tokens":36402,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1019},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1dad8c38-f7f9-4b29-a20f-bfe5c5522b3